OL,3,CWho is responsible for the Summerland
OL,4,Cdisaster?
OL,6,FThe Summerland disaster is regarded as
OL,7,Fthe Isle of Man's greatest tragedy -
OL,8,Fbut who was responsible?
OL,10,FA total of and 80 more were seriously
OL,11,Finjured after a fire spread through a
OL,12,Fleisure centre on 2 August 1973.
OL,14,FThe conclusion of a public inquiry
OL,15,Fmarked the event as 'death by
OL,16,Fmisadventure', but many of the
OL,17,Fsurvivors want this overturned.
OL,19,FA public inquiry, titled 'The
OL,20,FSummerland Fire Commission' (SFC), was
OL,21,Freleased in May 1974.
