OL,3,CWho is responsible for the Summerland
OL,4,Cdisaster?
OL,6,FGalbestos, a flammable material,
OL,7,Fcovered the lower levels, Oroglas
OL,8,Fpanels were on the upper levels and
OL,9,Fbehind the Galbestos, was an internal
OL,10,Fwall of combustible plastic-coated
OL,11,FDecalin.
OL,13,FAs the fire spread inside, it met the
OL,14,FOroglas which began melting with
OL,15,Fmolten plastic, burning people below -
OL,16,Fthe roof burnt out in around 10
OL,17,Fminutes.
