OL,3,CWho is responsible for the Summerland
OL,4,Cdisaster?
OL,6,FThe inquiry also highlighted that the
OL,7,FIsle of Man's fire regulations had
OL,8,Fbeen waived, stating that "the
OL,9,Fexternal walls of any building shall
OL,10,Fbe non-combustible throughout and have
OL,11,Fa fire resistance of two hours".
OL,13,FBut the report claimed that "neither
OL,14,FOroglas nor Colour Galbestos complied
OL,15,Fwith these rules".
OL,17,FWhat were the 'Factors in the Loss of
OL,18,FLife' according to the inquiry?
OL,20,FWhat do survivors want for the future?
